    <title>Calling all SOE Critics-you have a choice</title>
    <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=SOE&amp;message.id=3674</link>
    <description>&lt;div&gt;Whether or not this was its intended purpose, this folder has become a focal point for a tremendous amount of negative criticism aimed at SOE. The community on the servers seems far nicer than the community that hangs out here constantly grousing about what is right/wrong/whatever with EQ.  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Apparently, for the critics, SOE did (or didn't do) something each of you thought they should, and they are somehow ultimately to blame for your various forms of misery.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I beg to differ with you my fellow players.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;It is not SOE that is to blame for your problems with EQ. Each of you chooses to keep paying for access. By doing so, each of you is making a conscious decision to endorse &lt;strong&gt;everything&lt;/strong&gt; about EQ: the good, the bad, the ugly, and the indifferent.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;So it really comes down to a choice: If whatever problems you have with the game are such that it is no longer fun, and you no longer wish to lend any sort of endorsement to the product: end your patronage, sever ties, delete your account, uninstall the program, find another game to play.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Should you choose to remain, you are accepting the fact that you will not always be pleased by the changes SOE chooses to make to EQ, but overall, you believe that the experience of playing EQ is still enjoyable enough for you to to continue to give it your time, effort, and money.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Our time here would be better spent discussing what we love about the game and ways to enjoy playing it, as well as, providing &lt;em&gt;constructive criticism &lt;/em&gt;that helps make the game more enjoyable for everyone.&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    <pubDate>Wed, 08 Mar 2006 08:58:56 GMT</pubDate>
    <managingEditor>starsabre1</managingEditor>
    <dc:creator>starsabre1</dc:creator>
    <dc:date>2006-03-08T08:58:56Z</dc:date>
    <item>
      <title>Calling all SOE Critics-you have a choice</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=SOE&amp;message.id=3674#M3674</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;Whether or not this was its intended purpose, this folder has become a focal point for a tremendous amount of negative criticism aimed at SOE. The community on the servers seems far nicer than the community that hangs out here constantly grousing about what is right/wrong/whatever with EQ.  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Apparently, for the critics, SOE did (or didn't do) something each of you thought they should, and they are somehow ultimately to blame for your various forms of misery.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I beg to differ with you my fellow players.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;It is not SOE that is to blame for your problems with EQ. Each of you chooses to keep paying for access. By doing so, each of you is making a conscious decision to endorse &lt;strong&gt;everything&lt;/strong&gt; about EQ: the good, the bad, the ugly, and the indifferent.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;So it really comes down to a choice: If whatever problems you have with the game are such that it is no longer fun, and you no longer wish to lend any sort of endorsement to the product: end your patronage, sever ties, delete your account, uninstall the program, find another game to play.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Should you choose to remain, you are accepting the fact that you will not always be pleased by the changes SOE chooses to make to EQ, but overall, you believe that the experience of playing EQ is still enjoyable enough for you to to continue to give it your time, effort, and money.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Our time here would be better spent discussing what we love about the game and ways to enjoy playing it, as well as, providing &lt;em&gt;constructive criticism &lt;/em&gt;that helps make the game more enjoyable for everyone.&lt;/div&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Wed, 08 Mar 2006 08:58:56 GMT</pubDate>
