    <item>
      <title>Re: Calling all SOE Critics-you have a choice</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=SOE&amp;message.id=3885#M3885</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Critique &lt;strong&gt;is&lt;/strong&gt; welcome here.  Feedback is a wonderful tool to help the developers.  Good feedback and bad.  Do not be afraid of letting the production and development teams know how you feel about an issue.  Players like you and I make the game go 'round.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It is not the feedback that causes people to go at each other's throats.  It's how the passion of the opinion is portrayed on both sides of any arguement, as well as the avenue in which the feedback is expressed.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Do you not like a certain aspect of gameplay?&lt;/em&gt;  You're welcome to mention that in a thread already established.  The search function is a wonderful tool to find conversations in progress (being careful not to bump 3 year old threads, of course).  Be respectful of your fellow posters when you do so.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you feel you're very passionate about an issue, write your response up in notepad, leave it for an hour or overnight, and then read it over again to see if there's any better way you could word it to respectfully and professionally get your opinion out.  Is it constructive, or is it a rant that doesn't provide much meat for the developers or community to pick from it?  Does it attack your fellow community members or does it pinpoint the issue(s) at hand?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You can also utilize the /feedback in-game.  While this cannot garner any community feedback and it may not get you a direct tell in response to your feedback, this does go directly to development to help assist with gameplay.  Be descriptive and direct, clear and concise, and you may very well see your response as a nice change listed in the next patch update.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Do you not like a certain aspect of customer service or community moderation?&lt;/em&gt;  Don't post it on the public forums.  This is not the correct avenue for the feedback, as stated by the Forum Rules stickied to every subforum.  While it may feel great to get that heated rant off your chest where others may agree with you on the issue, the people who need to see that feedback simply wont be able to give it the attention it needs, if they see it at all. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;For CS commendations or complaints, you can email &lt;a target="_blank" href="mailto:eqcs@soe.sony.com"&gt;eqcs@soe.sony.com&lt;/a&gt; - For moderation commendations or complaints, you can PM Kytherea or use the Report Abuse link below the post in question.  In both of those cases, the right people will see it, and see it much faster, and your commendation or complaint can have the most impact.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;No matter your opinion on subjects, whether you really like the way SOE is taking the games it produces or you have some major valid concern with anything, your feedback is welcome.  Be considerate, voice it with clarity rather than venom and flames, and use the right avenue for each type of feedback you wish to share.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Oh, and remember that each person is different.  Opinions will differ.  You don't have to agree with what each poster says, but you should respect them. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;No one has to leave because their opinion differs on one matter or another.  Everyone is welcome here.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;EDIT: Grammar hates me tonight.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by HH-Sidra on &lt;span class="date_text"&gt;03-29-2006&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="time_text"&gt;07:57 PM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
